<dl id="n12151g"> <dt class="nbunit"><a name="n12" href="#n12151g">N12 (VI.B.14)</a>:  <a href="../../FF/fnbs/n12all.htm#n12151g"> 151(g)</a></dt> <dd> <blockquote> Pelagius (Scotobrit) / stuffed with Scotch porridge / pultibus pregravatus / Jerome</blockquote> <dd class="well"> <blockquote class="sources">Jerome (Pr&aelig;f. in Jerem., lib. I and III) ridicules him as a &ldquo;Scot&rdquo; (loc. cit., &ldquo;havet enim progeniem Scoti&aelig; gentis de Britannorum vicinia&rdquo;) &hellip; &ldquo;stuffed with Scottish porridge&rdquo; (<i>Scotorum pultibus pr&aelig;gravatus</i>) <small> <a name="CEPEL" href="../../FF/fdra/fdex.htm#CEPEL"><cite title="source">&ldquo;Pelagius&rdquo;</cite></a> <cite a>Catholic Encyclopaedia</cite></a> (1911) 604b</small></blockquote> <mm class="note">Raphael transcription: <a name="c12155g" href="c12all.htm#c12155g">VI.C.12:155(g)</a>, <a name="c12155h" href="c12all.htm#c12155h">VI.C.12:155(h)</a>, <a name="c12155i" href="c12all.htm#c12155i">VI.C.12:155(i)</a> </mm></dd> </dd></dl>
